      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "a3e2f3ece1f9ccfc",
      "text": "Verification of site ownership is just the beginning of the dance with google analytics. One must add their javascript to each web page to be analyzed. This code contains an identifying key which is reported back to google. The magic of analytics is that nearly every site operator uses this free service. This ubiquity allows google to watch people move from site to site. They then slice up this global view and report fragments back to each site operator with charts and graphs of visitor behavior. I logged into analytics last night and found that they now offer reports on individual visitors tracked over time. This is all pretty spooky and not at all aligned with my own vision of public service.\n"
